cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper proposes a deep learning approach for SAR image despeckling, which involves using a dilated residual network. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of skip connections and residual learning, which are common techniques in deep learning, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of dilated convolutions and the lightweight structure of the network could also suggest a connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with image processing, which could place it in the cs.MM (Multimedia) category.
